# Monoceros global env (monoceros-config.env)
#
# Secrets shared across ALL your containers. This file is gitignored and
# never committed. Values here are the fallback; a per-container
# container-configs/<name>.env overrides them for that one container.
#
# Format is plain KEY=value, one per line, no quotes, '#' starts a comment.
#
# ===================================================================
# Git provider tokens (private repo clone/push + gh/glab auth)
# ===================================================================
#
# Monoceros clones and pushes private repos, and authenticates the gh /
# glab CLIs inside the container, using a Personal Access Token per host.
# Nothing (no gh/glab/git) needs to be installed on the host for this.
#
# Variable name:  MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__<host>
#
#   Take the repo's host and replace every character that is not a letter
#   or digit with an underscore:
#
#     github.com          ->  MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__github_com
#     gitlab.com          ->  MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__gitlab_com
#     gitlab.example.de   ->  MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__gitlab_example_de
#     github.acme-corp.io ->  MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__github_acme_corp_io
#
# Which token to create:
#
#   GitHub  ->  a classic token with the `repo` scope
#               https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   GitLab  ->  a personal access token with the `api` scope
#               https://gitlab.com/-/user_settings/personal_access_tokens
#
#   Set an expiry. The same token covers git (clone/push) and the CLI
#   (PRs / merge requests / issues), so create it broad enough for the
#   work you do.
#
# Uncomment and set the ones you need:
#
# MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__github_com=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# MONOCEROS_GIT_TOKEN__gitlab_com=glpat-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
